      "content": "The term \"clean\" in energy is relative, as no energy source is perfectly benign. While mining and blade disposal are real concerns, they are often outweighed by the massive, continuous emissions and climate damage caused by fossil fuels like natural gas. The industry is actively addressing these lifecycle impacts through better material science and recycling initiatives. Therefore, while not perfectly pristine, wind energy remains a vastly superior and necessary transition tool compared to combustion-based power.",
